The paper deals with control barrier functions for robotic systems, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of a supervised machine learning approach for estimating the barrier function from sensor data suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also mentions the use of a support vector machine classifier, which is a common machine learning technique (cs.AI). Finally, the use of LiDAR for sensing suggests a possible connection to computer vision (cs.CV).
